Members of the Welsh National Assembly fear they will be called muppets
Among some of the members of the National Assembly, there was a dismay. This is the result of a proposal to change their title to Members of the Welsh Parliament.
The idea was created in connection with plans to replace the assembly with the Welsh Parliament.
Members of the assembly from all sides of the political scene are concerned that they can be mocked.
One Labour MP expressed concerns about his group, saying that the new name rhymes with the Welsh words "twp" and "pwp".
For readers outside Wales: in Welsh, the word "twp" means stupid, and the word "pwp" means feces.
One Plaid Cymru party politician stated that his group was "dissatisfied" with the proposal and presented other solutions.
A member of the Welsh Conservative Party said that his party was "open" to change the name. However, he pointed out that the word "MWP" was very similar to the word "muppet".
In this case, the Welsh letter "w" is pronounced similar to the letter "u" in the English dialect of Yorkshire.
The assembly committee, which is currently working on a bill amending the name, took the following position: "Naturally, the final decision on the future title of the members of the assembly will belong to them."
The 2017 Government of Wales Act gave the Welsh National Assembly the right to change its name.
In June, the committee published the results of the public consultation on the proposal, and the conversion of the assembly to the Welsh Parliament gained broad support.
In addition, the committee supported the proposal to change the title of members of the assembly to the "Wales Member of Parliament", that is, the WMP in English, although the term "MWP" was the most popular among the public.
Members of the assembly offer alternative solutions. The difficulty of reaching consensus is a nuisance to Elin Jones, the chairman of the assembly, who should present a bill in the coming weeks.
The law introducing reforms will also take into account other changes in the way the assembly works, including the rules for recalling members and the structure of the committee system.
Members of the National Assembly will be able to vote on their future title when discussing the bill.
