New German warship again delayed
The latest frigate of the German Navy should be put into service in 2014 to replace the ageing warships of the Cold War, but this will not happen at least next year due to defective systems and rising costs at an alarming rate, as reported by the local media.
The release of "Rheinland-Pfalz", the main ship of the new frigate of the Baden-Wuerttemberg class, was moved to the first half of 2019, as reported by the newspaper Die Zeit, citing the words of a military spokesperson.
